---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Section, Button } from '@/components/ui';
---

<Layout
  title="Our Story - Sharing Hindu Heritage Through Children's Books | Roots On Rise"
  description="Discover how Krithika's journey as a mother inspired Roots On Rise - creating Hindu children's books that connect kids to Indian culture, mythology, and heritage through beautiful storytelling."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <Section background="tertiary" container="md">
    <div class="text-center">
      <h1 class="font-title font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-dark mb-6">
        <span class="text-primary">our</span> story
      </h1>
      <p class="text-dark/70 text-lg">
        A mother's journey to share the beauty of Hindu culture with the world.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Story Content -->
  <Section container="md">
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-title font-bold text-3xl text-dark mb-8">
        üôè Namaste!
      </h2>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Welcome to our world of cultural exploration! I'm so glad you are here.
      </p>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I am <strong class="text-primary">Krithika</strong>. I play many roles in life, but the one I'm most proud of is to be the mother to my two lovely, beautiful daughters <strong>Aarna & Aira</strong>. As a new mother, I soon found myself teaching my young girls about the rich cultural heritage of the land I come from - <em>India (Bharat)</em>, and telling them stories about our mythology, our many Gods and Goddesses.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-tertiary p-8 rounded-lg my-8">
        <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed italic">
          "I soon realized that most products - books, games, and related products did not spark curiosity in children to learn more about India, and did not evoke pride in our rich civilization."
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        This drove me to write my first Children's Illustration book <strong class="text-primary">"The Marvelous Hindu Deities"</strong>, which quickly became a favorite with my kids, and many others like them.
      </p>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Encouraged by the book's popularity, and driven by a deep sense of passion for sharing our rich South Asian heritage & culture with the rest of the world, I created <strong>Roots On Rise</strong>, a platform to unveil cultural treasures through playful learning and personal discovery.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-title font-bold text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-6">
        Our Mission
      </h3>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Our products are designed to bring engaging and immersive experiences into our homes, and cultivate a deep connection to our collective roots, mythology and history.
      </p>

      <p class="text-dark/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Join us on this exciting adventure as we craft products that not only entertain but also serve as windows into the vibrant tapestry of rich traditions. Together, let's nurture a global community of young learners who celebrate their rich cultural identities!
      </p>

      <div class="bg-dark text-light p-8 rounded-lg my-8">
        <p class="text-xl font-title font-bold mb-2">Thanks for joining us.</p>
        <p class="text-light/70">‚Äî Krithika, Founder of Roots On Rise</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <Button asChild>
        <a href="/books">Explore Our Books</a>
      </Button>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Layout>
